errors.message: maximal_tcs_is_mcs theorem appears mathematically false. A set maximal in TCS (temporally-saturated consistent supersets) may not be MCS (maximal consistent set) because: when φ = F(ψ), φ ∉ M, neg(φ) ∉ M, and ψ ∉ M, insert φ M is consistent but fails temporal saturation.
errors.recommendation: Consider RecursiveSeed approach (tasks 864/880) which builds witnesses into the construction from the start
